  "title": "Even though vs Even if - English In A Minute",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 179.0,
      "end_time": 2719.0,
      "text": "Hi, I'm Phil from BBC Learning English."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2720.0,
      "end_time": 5649.0,
      "text": "Today, I'm going to tell you the difference between"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5649.0,
      "end_time": 8580.0,
      "text": "'even though' and 'even if'."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8580.0,
      "end_time": 11280.0,
      "text": "Now, we use them both for emphasis"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 11280.0,
      "end_time": 13600.0,
      "text": "but they don't mean the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13600.0,
      "end_time": 16939.0,
      "text": "We use 'even though' to introduce something that's true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16940.0,
      "end_time": 19610.0,
      "text": "but might be a little bit unexpected."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 19610.0,
      "end_time": 22000.0,
      "text": "It's a bit like 'despite'."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 22000.0,
      "end_time": 23600.0,
      "text": "Even though I hate driving,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 23600.0,
      "end_time": 26300.0,
      "text": "I'm still going to Scotland by car."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 26300.0,
      "end_time": 28560.0,
      "text": "Even though I hate tennis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 28560.0,
      "end_time": 30439.0,
      "text": "I'm still going to watch the final."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 30440.0,
      "end_time": 35320.0,
      "text": "We use 'even if' to introduce something hypothetical,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 35320.0,
      "end_time": 37320.0,
      "text": "so it might not be real."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 37320.0,
      "end_time": 39600.0,
      "text": "Even if it's sunny when we're in Scotland,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 39600.0,
      "end_time": 40960.0,
      "text": "I'm not going swimming."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 40960.0,
      "end_time": 44280.0,
      "text": "Even if you paid me, I wouldn't watch that film."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 44280.0,
      "end_time": 47820.0,
      "text": "So, 'even though' is for things that are true"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 47820.0,
      "end_time": 49280.0,
      "text": "but unexpected,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 49280.0,
      "end_time": 52380.0,
      "text": "and 'even if' is for things that are hypothetical,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 52380.0,
      "end_time": 53800.0,
      "text": "so they might not be real."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 53800.0,
      "end_time": 55779.0,
      "text": "Even though they look the same,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 55780.0,
      "end_time": 58860.0,
      "text": "they are different â€“ even if you didn't notice at first!"
